			</td>
			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">ulfalizer wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The output is determined by fine_x I think, which acts as a pointer into the left/top shift reg. That's why you need 16 bits - to make sure you never &quot;run out&quot; of pixels even if fine_x is set to 7.</div><br /><br />Yeah, it's a tad weird though, since the value of fine_x really determines bit (15 - fine_x) is output.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;FEDCBA98 76543210<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;00110011 00110011<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;^<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;|<br />fine_x(0)+<br /><br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;FEDCBA98 76543210<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;00110011 00110011<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; ^<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; |<br />fine_x(7)-------+</div><br /><br />Conceptually, the background does the following every dot for output (C++):<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">// get bits from shifters<br />u8_t attr = ( attr_shifter ) &amp; 0x3U;<br />u8_t bit0 = ( bit0_shifter &gt;&gt; ( fine_x ^ 0xFU ) ) &amp; 0x1U;<br />u8_t bit1 = ( bit1_shifter &gt;&gt; ( fine_x ^ 0xFU ) ) &amp; 0x1U;<br /><br />// clock shifters to the next pixel<br />bit0_shifter = u16_t( bit0_shifter &lt;&lt; 1 );<br />bit1_shifter = u16_t( bit1_shifter &lt;&lt; 1 );<br /><br />// 'clock' in new data if necessary<br />if ( hclock &amp; 0x8U )<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; attr_shifter&nbsp; = u8_t( attr_shifter &lt;&lt; 2 ) | attr_fetch; // attr_shifter is only clocked once per tile (every 8 dots)<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; bit0_shifter |= bit0_fetch;<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; bit1_shifter |= bit1_fetch;<br />}<br /><br />u8_t color = ( attr &lt;&lt; 2 ) | ( bit1 &lt;&lt; 1 ) | bit0;<br /><br />if ( color ) // don't ouput 0<br />{<br />&nbsp; &nbsp; output_bg( color );<br />}</div></div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

